subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
—In previous literature, described as smallbodied (‘‘diminutive’’) and short-limbed, with unequal inner and outer metatarsal tubercle sizes; distinct subarticular tubercles; barely visible supernumerary tubercles; no vomerine odontophores (
Taylor 1936
); rounded canthus; two palmar tubercles (
Taylor 1942
).
